National Meeting Commemorates Birthday of Kim Hyok 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- A national meeting took place at the People's Palace of Culture today in commemoration of the centenary of birth of Kim Hyok, a revolutionary fighter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were senior officials of the Party, the army and the state and the chairperson of a friendly party and officials of the Party and armed forces organs and social bodies, ministries and national institutions and servicepersons of the Korean People's Army and labor innovators and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Born into a peasant's family in North Phyongan Province on Oct. 11 1907, Kim Hyok reached a turning point in his life after finding the course of life as a true revolutionary under the outstanding leadership of President Kim Il Sung. Kim Hyok acted as a core member of the Down-with-Imperialism Union and the Young Communist League and member of the first party organization and chief editor of the revolutionary publication "Bolshevik" and commanding member of the Korean Revolutionary Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea, in a report said that Kim Hyok held the President as the sun of the nation and the leader of revolution in high esteem at the dawn of the revolutionary cause of Juche and considered him as the central figure of the unity and the leadership, thereby making an outstanding contribution to creating a new history of unity and cohesion of the revolutionary ranks centered on the leader for the first time in the history of the Korean revolutionary movement and ushering in a new era of the struggle victoriously advancing the revolution, achieving the perfect unity of the leader and the popular masses in thinking and faith based on comradeship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ardent reverence shown by Kim Hyok for the President, greatly attracted by his personality as a great man found a more vivid expression in creating and disseminating the revolutionary hymn "Star of Korea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyok's intense loyalty to the President displayed in resolutely upholding the idea and cause of the President at all times found a striking manifestation in that Kim Hyok faithfully implemented with fervent enthusiasm the tasks given by the President, regarding them as the most honorable and sacred revolutionary ones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyok's noble and strong revolutionary faith and principles were strikingly expressed in his heroic self-sacrificing spirit in which he died a heroic death in the worst adversity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President considered Kim Hyok as an eternal revolutionary comrade with profound loving care all his life, remembering him as a revolutionary comrade-in-arms who left unforgettable impressions on him during his youth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il highly praised Kim Hyok as a model of the genuine revolutionary fighters and called on all servicepersons and people to learn from his revolutionary spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Ki Nam underscored the need to invariably and firmly preserve and carry forward the noble ideological and moral assets gained by the revolutionary forerunners despite any changing situation and thus give steady continuity to the Juche-based traditions of the Korean revolution generation after generation.

Wreaths Laid before Bust of Kim Hyok 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were placed before the bust of revolutionary martyr Kim Hyok at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong Thursday on the occasion of the centenary of his birth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen standing before the bust was a wreath sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Kim Il Chol, Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Ki Nam and leading officials of ministries, national institutions and working people's organizations and officials of party and power organs in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Laid before the bust were wreaths in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, ministries, national institutions and party and power organs and working people's organizations in Pyongyang and bouquets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of Kim Hyok who performed undying feats in the early period of the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle.

Dancing Parties Held to Mark WPK's Birthday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Dancing parties of youth and students took place in different parts of the country on Oct. 10 in celebration of the 62nd anniversary of the foundation of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dancing parties of youth and students began to the tune of the song "Please Accept Best Wishes of People" in different places of Pyongyang such as the plazas of the Monument to Party Founding, the Tower of the Juche Idea and the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They danced to the tune of songs "Our General Is Best", "The Youth Shines Thanks to the Workers' Party", "It Is Pride of Our Party", "Let Us Youth Uphold Our Party", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the pleasant dancing parties evinced their revolutionary enthusiasm to steadily glorify the honor of being young vanguard in the worthwhile drive to uphold the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il and to carry to completion the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered from Mt. Paektu following the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar dancing parties took place in different parts of the country such as Phyongsong, Sinuiju, Hamhung and Kanggye cities.

Credentials to Kim Yong Nam 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, received credentials from Thai Ambassador e.p. to the DPRK Rathakit Manathat at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il and Thai embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After receiving the credentials, Kim had a talk with the ambassador.

FM of DPRK Meets New Thai Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun met and had a talk with new Thai Ambassador e.p. to the DPRK Rathakit Manathat who paid a courtesy call on him on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were officials concerned and Thai embassy officials.

Greetings to President of Equatorial Guinea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Obiang Nguema Mbasogo, President of Equatorial Guinea, on Oct. 5 on the occasion of the 39th anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wishing the people of Equatorial Guinea peace, prosperity and social progress in the future, too, Kim in the message reaffirmed the consistent stand of the DPRK to boost the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries.

Photo Exhibition Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The Cuban embassy in Pyongyang arranged a photo exhibition at the Chollima House of Culture Thursday on the occasions of the 40th death anniversary of Che Guevara and the month of solidarity with the Cuban patriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Minister of Education Kim Yong Jin who is chairman of the DPRK-Cuban Solidarity Committee, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Pak Jae Gyong, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, Kim Hyong Jun, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, officials concerned and working people in the city of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there were Cuban Ambassador to the DPRK Jose Manuel Galego Montano and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ambassador in a speech at the exhibition referred to the fact that President Kim Il Sung received Che Guevara on a visit to the DPRK after the victory in the Cuban revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the Cuban people had enjoyed solidarity from the fraternal Korean people in the course of their struggle for the release of the Cuban patriots unreasonably detained by the United States. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Jae Chol in a speech said that Che Guevara, an internationalist soldier, devoted his all to the freedom and emancipation of the oppressed popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He extended full support and solidarity to the Cuban people in their just struggle to set free Cuban patriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants looked round photos showing Kim Il Sung receiving Che Guevara and activities conducted by the latter.

Kim Jong Il Sends Birthday Spread to Former Unconverted Long-term Prisoner 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il on October 10 sent a birthday spread to Yun Hui Bo, former unconverted long-term prisoner, on his 90th birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Born into a poor peasant's family on October 10, Juche 6 (1917) in Kwangju, Kyonggi Province, south Korea, Yun Hui Bo could not realize his wishes due to the national discrimination and maltreatment of the Japanese imperialists, subject to hard labor in his boyhood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was arrested by the enemies while waging a heroic and sacred struggle true to the cause of national reunification started by President Kim Il Sung, but remained true to his faith and sense of obligation as a revolutionary soldier behind bars fraught with the danger of death for 25 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il made sure that he was awarded the title of Hero of the Republic and the National Reunification Prize and has repeatedly shown profound loving care for him.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Thai Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the delegation of the Organization for the Study of the Juche Idea of Thailand on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was conveyed to an official concerned by Chairman of the organization Songchit Pullarp, head of the delegation.

Japan's Hostile Policy towards DPRK Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Japan recently decided to ask the countries concerned to help it in its efforts to have a resolution on the non-existent "north Korea's human rights issue" adopted at the United Nations in a bid to press for the solution of the "abduction issue." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, it is begging the U.S. not to de-list north Korea as a "sponsor of terrorism" unless the "abduction issue" is solved. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard, Rodong Sinmun today observes in a signed commentary: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is shameless and ridiculous, indeed, for the Japanese reactionaries to take issue with somebody's "human rights issue" instead of honestly admitting, apologizing and compensating for their past human rights abuses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As far as the "abduction issue" is concerned, it had already found a solution thanks to the sincere and humanitarian efforts of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a far-fetched assertion for Japan to persistently raise a hue and cry over the "abduction issue," demanding the DPRK bring the dead persons to life and send them back to Japan. It is nothing but a clumsy ploy to use the "abduction issue" as a card to achieve its sinister political purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present Japanese authorities would be well advised to draw a lesson from the miserable end of the preceding "Cabinet" which staked its political fate on the solution of the "abduction issue."  Nevertheless, the present Japanese authorities are behaving quite contrary to this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some days ago, the chief Cabinet secretary of Japan said the regime was replaced by a new one but the basic stand on the policy towards the DPRK would remain unchanged. This goes to clearly prove the wrong intention of Japan. The present Japanese authorities are keen to use the "abduction issue" as a sort of lever. This only reveals their intention to follow in the footsteps of the preceding "Cabinet" which regarded it as its policy to have the "abduction issue" settled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the six-party talks aimed at discussing the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula are to make progress, it is important, above all, for the participating nations to earnestly approach the talks with a sincere attitude and stance on the main purport of the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is now persistently considering the "abduction issue" as part of the agenda of the six-party talks. This attitude and stand compel the DPRK to reconsider whether Japan is qualified to participate in the talks. Japan seems to be keen on deliberately throwing obstacles in the way of the six-party talks and thus bar the peninsula from being denuclearized in a bid to secure a justification for nuclear weaponization and realize its ambition to become a military power and launch overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such trite artifice will only invite derision and criticism from the world people and precipitate Japan's isolation and destruction.

Photo Exhibition of Koguryo Tomb Mural Paintings Opened
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- A photo exhibition of the Koguryo tomb mural paintings was opened at the Korean Central History Museum here on Thursday under the co-sponsorship of the Yonhap News of south Korea and the Kyodo News of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the exhibition hall are photos of Koguryo mural paintings including those in King Kogukwon's Mausoleum (Anak Tomb No. 3) and Tokhung-ri tomb, which are listed as the world's cultural heritages, and those in middle- and big-size tombs in Kangso. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the opening ceremony were Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Hong Son Ok, its vice-chairperson, Kim Chang Gwang, deputy director general of the Korean Central News Agency, Pak Kyong Chol, vice-chairman of the National Reconciliation Council, officials concerned and working people in the city of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there were a delegation of the Yonhap News of south Korea led by Director General Kim Ki So and a delegation of the Kyodo News of Japan led by President Satoshi Ishikawa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the ceremony said that the Koguryo tomb mural paintings which retain their original appearance to shine brightly despite the passage of many years are precious treasures associated with the soul and resourcefulness of the Korean nation and cultural heritage common to humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibition will contribute to deepening the understanding of the time-honored history and culture of the Korean nation, they stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A reception was held at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel as regards the opening of the exhibition on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibition will run till Nov. 10.

DPRK Women's Football Team Upsets Japanese Rival 3:1
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The DPRK and Japanese teams met in Group A qualifying round of the 2007 Asian Women's U-19 Football Championships in Chongqing, China, on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's equalizing goal came at the 24th minute after the kick-off, after which the second shot was sent home at the 18th minute and the third at the 25th minute in the second half to oust Japan 3:1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@By finishing the winner in Group A, the DPRK team will compete with the Chinese team, the runner-up in Group B, in the semi-finals on Oct. 13.

Ryongaksan Pleasure Park Renovated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Mt. Ryongak situated in Mangyongdae District, Pyongyang City has been renovated as a people's pleasure park. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A new road extending 4.5km was built from the Mangyongdae Children's Union Camp to the top of the highest Tae Peak of Mt. Ryongak to form a loop road network in the mountain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And the Songdok Pavilion on Tae Peak was renovated and an observation platform on a rock in front of the Pobun Temple built in a unique way so that the visitors can feast their eyes on general view of the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Three mountaineering roads leading to Tae Peak along the curious rocks and valleys were improved more conveniently and over 100 animal sculptures, resting sites and public service facilities were built in different parts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scenery of Mt. Ryongak which has hundreds of species of plants and many natural monuments becomes more beautiful when October is ushered in.

Russian Party Chairperson Visits DPRK Embassy in Moscow
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- S. Umalatova, chairperson of the Party for Peace and Unity of Russia, paid a congratulatory visit to the DPRK embassy in Moscow on October 6 on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 81st anniversary of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She laid a big floral basket before a full-length portrait of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il standing together and paid a tribute to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying there is no such an invincible party as the WPK founded by the President and led by Kim Jong Il in the world, she stressed that not only the Korean people but the world progressive humankind will surely emerge victorious thanks to Kim Jong Il.

Birthday of WPK Marked in Foreign Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Seminars, a book and photo exhibition and film shows took place in Italy, Nepal and Peru from September 29 to October 3 on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Several figures at the seminars explained and proved the originality and the greatness of the Songun policy and experience gained by the WPK in party building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Miriam Pellegrini Ferri, chairman of the Italian Committee for the Study of Songun Idea for Independence and Sovereignty, said that the WPK could augment its might in every way, guide the people of the DPRK to victory and defend and develop socialism despite all sorts of trials and difficulties of history as it has had Kim Jong Il at its head. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that as long as the WPK is led by Kim Jong Il, it will steadily grow stronger as the guide of the cause of Songun and fully demonstrate its might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The former minister of Information and Communication of Nepal and Lam Prid Paswan, former vice-president of the Senate of Nepal, said that the WPK has firmly maintained its position as the greatest party in the 21st century, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Victor Oliva Miguel, general secretary of the Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru, said that one of the exploits performed by the WPK is the successful solution of the issue of youth, stressing that the youth movement in the DPRK is now greeting its most shining heyday thanks to Kim Jong Il's idea of attaching importance to youth and fully demonstrating its invincible might in the anti-U.S. struggle and in the struggle to defend socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the film shows watched DPRK film "We Will Follow You to the End of This World." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar held in Nepal adopted a congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il.

Information Bulletin Issued in Mexico to Mark Birthday of WPK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism issued information bulletin No.3 on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin carried an article titled "We serve the people!" together with a photograph of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin said in the article that there are many political parties in the world but it is only the WPK which is considering the will and wishes of the popular masses as the starting point in shaping the party's line and policies under the uplifted slogan of "We serve the people!" It noted that Kim Il Sung always went among the people and shaped line and policies in keeping with people's will and wishes and the specific conditions of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The large-scale land realignment and the gravity-driven waterway projects which radically changed the appearance of the socialist countryside of the DPRK in recent years had been designed by Kim Jong Il on the road of ceaseless field guidance, the bulletin noted, referring in detail to the popular policies of the WPK which has deemed it an iron rule to always place the interests of the people above all and looked after the life of the people in a responsible manner.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also carried an article introducing the history of the DPRK and a photograph of the Chollima Statue.

Birthday of WPK Celebrated by Chinese Crewmen
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Haeju, October 10 (KCNA) -- A meeting of Chinese crewmen was held at the Haeju Port on October 9 to celebrate the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the captains and crewmen of Chinese ships: the "Shun Fa 7" and the "Liao Chang Yu 6804".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting said that the people of the DPRK have built a powerful socialist country under the wise leadership of the WPK founded by President Kim Il Sung, stressing that his great exploits would be always remembered by the people of the DPRK and progressive humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Russia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" was brought out in booklet by the Maritime Territorial Regional Committee of the Communist Party of the Russian Federation on the occasion of the 62nd anniversary of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work published on October 2, Juche 84 (1995), is an immortal great programme of party building and activities proudly reviewing the glorious history of the WPK, which paved a new way of building a revolutionary party in the era of independence under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung, and clearly indicating the road of developing the WPK eternally as the party of the President.

GNP's Servile Attitude toward Outside Forces Denounced in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils reportedly released a statement on October 4 calling for the punishment of the Grand National Party, the pro-U.S. flunkeyist traitor party which stands against the nation, swimming against the flow of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that Ri Myong Bak, "presidential candidate" from the GNP, was spurned by his master while attempting to gratify his wild ambition to seize power with the backing of the United States, the statement said this was a deserving reward to the pro-U.S. flunkeyist traitor party which is selling off the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people will never pardon the group of flunkeyist traitors and will surely deal a setback to the GNP in the on-coming "presidential election," said the statement.

Kim Jong Il presencia "Arirang" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 11 de octubre (ATCC) -- En ocasion del 62o aniversario de la fundacion del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, se ofrecio el dia 10 por la noche en el capitalino Estadio Primero de Mayo la funcion gimnastico-artistica masiva "Arirang" condecorada con el "Premio Kim Il Sung".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El estadio estaba ataviado con la maqueta del monte Paektu, que simboliza las gloriosas tradiciones revolucionarias del PTC, y los luminicos electricos de varios tipos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mientras resonaba la musica de bienvenida, salio a la tribuna el Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del PTC y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Simultaneamente, se dispararon los fuegos artificiales y se detonaron las aclamaciones de "!viva!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mientras tanto, en la pizarra humana aparecio la oracion de "Rendimos maximo tributo al gran Lider, fundador del PTC" y en la cancha se levantaron oleajes de flores y baile. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los asientos de la tribuna se distinguian tambien los cuadros del partido, el Estado y el ejercito Kim Yong Nam, Kim Yong Il, Ri Yong Mu, Kim Kyok Sik, Kim Il Chol, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Jong Gak, Kim Kuk Thae, Kim Jung Rin, Kim Ki Nam y Choe Yong Rim, el presidente del Comite Central del Partido Social-Democrata de Corea Kim Yong Dae, los jefes de departamento del CC del PTC y los funcionarios directivos de las instituciones de fuerzas armadas y las entidades de masas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Vieron la funcion tambien los funcionarios de los organos del partido, las fuerzas armadas y el Poder, entidades sociales, ministerios, organos centrales y de las ramas de ciencia, educacion, cultura y arte, salud publica, prensa e informacion, los participantes en los actos por el 60o aniversario de la fundacion de la Escuela Revolucionaria de Mangyongdae y de la Escuela Revolucionaria Kang Pan Sok, uniformados del Ejercito Popular de Corea, hombres ameritados y trabajadores capitalinos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Fueron invitados los representantes diplomaticos y agregados militares de varios paises, los delegados de organizaciones internacionales y corresponsales, acreditados en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El espectaculo quedo iniciado mientras repercutia la melodia de la cancion "Arirang".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En sus episodios epicos la funcion mostro de modo impresionante la majestuosa fisonomia de la Corea del Juche, que bajo la guia del Presidente, trajo un cambio radical en la forja del destino nacional y marcha a pasos firmes hacia su futuro maravilloso manifestando su gallardo aspecto de la muy digna potencia independiente y el bastion del socialismo, y el potencial de la ferrea unidad monolitica en torno al PTC entre decenas de millones de militares y habitantes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Arranco efusivas ovaciones de los espectadores la "Arirang", caracterizada por la gran habilidad artistica de los ejecutantes y la perfecta armonia entre los originales aparatos escenograficos, luminicos electricos y equipos de iluminacion de varios tipos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Terminada la funcion, volvieron a resonar las aclamaciones de "vivas" y a lanzarse los fuegos artificiales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente Kim Jong Il respondio a los ejecutantes y la multitud, que le saludaban hospitalariamente, y felicito los exitos de la funcion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se mostro muy satisfecho por la excelente readaptacion de la "Arirang" y agradecio a todos los ejecutantes y creadores en nombre del CC del PTC, el Comite de Defensa Nacional y el gobierno, de la RPDC.

Acto central por centenario del nacimiento de Kim Hyok 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 11 de octubre (ATCC) -- Tuvo lugar el dia 11 en el capitalino Palacio Cultural del Pueblo el acto central por el 100o cumpleanos del combatiente revolucionario Kim Hyok. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion estuvieron presentes los cuadros del partido, el ejercito y el Estado, el presidente de partido amigo, los funcionarios de organismos del partido y las fuerzas armadas, entidades sociales, ministerios y organos centrales, oficiales y soldados del Ejercito Popular de Corea, innovadores laborales y trabajadores capitalinos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Kim Hyok, nacido el 11 de octubre de 1907 en una familia campesina de la provincia de Phyong-an del Norte, pudo entrar en la transicion de su vida y llevar la vida de revolucionario autentico gracias a la sabia guia del Presidente Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Siendo miembro medular de la Union para Derrotar al Imperialismo, la Union de la Juventud Comunista y la primera organizacion del partido, trabajo de redactor de la publicacion revolucionaria "Bolchevique" y de comandante del Ejercito Revolucionario de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El informe de la ocasion estuvo a cargo del secretario del CC del Partido del trabajo de Corea Kim Ki Nam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Ya desde los albores de la causa revolucionaria del Juche, Kim Hyok enaltecio al Presidente Kim Il Sung como Sol de la nacion, lider de la revolucion y centro de la unidad y de la direccion, comenzo el orador y prosiguio: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@De esta manera, el hizo una contribucion excepcional a dar inicio, por primera vez en la trayectoria del movimiento revolucionario coreano, a la nueva historia de la unidad y la cohesion de las filas revolucionarias cuyo centro es el lider y a la nueva epoca de lucha en que este y las masas populares conducen a la victoria la revolucion identificando la ideologia y la conviccion basadas en la camaraderia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La veneracion infinita de Kim Hyok, fascinado por la noble personalidad del Presidente Kim Il Sung, se manifesto patentemente en la creacion y divulgacion del himno revolucionario "Lucero de Corea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Su fidelidad absoluta a la idea y la causa del Presidente se corroboro en haber materializado hasta el fin con una pasion incomparable las tareas dadas por este considerandolas como la mision revolucionaria mas honrosa y sagrada. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La entereza revolucionaria de Kim Hyok se puso de pleno manifiesto en su espiritu de sacrificio heroico con que dio su vida cuando cayo en una situacion muy critica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Presidente lo recordaba durante toda su vida como un eterno companero de armas revolucionario que dejo huellas imborrables en su juventud. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente Kim Jong Il evaluo a Kim Hyok de ejemplo de verdadero combatiente revolucionario e instruyo a todos los oficiales y soldados del EPC y al pueblo que aprendieran su espiritu revolucionario. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Bajo cualesquier circunstancias, debemos mantener con firmeza y desarrollar invariablemente las nobles riquezas ideo-espirituales logradas por los precursores revolucionarios y continuar de generacion en generacion la estirpe jucheana de la Revolucion Coreana.
